ways-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDemis%20Hassabis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Thursday%20interview%20with%20entrepreneur%20Varun%20Mayya%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-leaders-india-summit-awkward-photo-hands-modi-altman-amodei-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIndia%20AI%20Impact%20Summit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Google%20DeepMind%20CEO%20said%20that%20AI%20is%20just%20like%20the%20internet.%20People%20can%20use%20it%20to%20learn%20all%20kinds%20of%20topics%2C%20or%20use%20it%20in%20ways%20that%20%26quot%3Bdegrade%26quot%3B%20their%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20AI%2C%20if%20you%20use%20it%20in%20a%20lazy%20way%2C%20it%20will%20make%20you%20worse%20at%20critical%20thinking%20and%20so%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20down%20to%20you%20as%20the%20individual.%20No%20one%20can%20help%20you%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20people%20need%20to%20be%20smart%20and%20use%20these%20technologies%20in%20ways%20that%20enhance%20their%20thinking%20rather%20than%20dull%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHassabis%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdemis-hassabis-ai-scaling-pushed-to-maximum-data-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecofounded%20DeepMind%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202010%2C%20which%20Google%20acquired%20in%202014.%20It%20merged%20with%20Google%20Brain%20in%202023%20to%20form%20Google%20DeepMind%2C%20the%20lab%20behind%20tools%20such%20as%20Gemini%20and%20Nano%20Banana.%20The%20CEO%20and%20a%20DeepMind%20coworker%2C%20John%20Jumper%2C%20were%20awarded%20the%202024%20Nobel%20Prize%20for%20Chemistry%20for%20their%20work%20on%20protein%20structure%20prediction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20gets%20incorporated%20into%20daily%20life%2C%20debates%20about%20its%20risks%20and%20rewards%20have%20intensified%2C%20with%20several%20tech%20leaders%20warning%20about%20the%20dangers%20of%20an%20overreliance%20on%20AI%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20tech%20billionaire%20Mark%20Cuban%20said%20that%20there%20are%20two%20types%20of%20people%20who%20use%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20generally%202%20types%20of%20LLM%20users%2C%20those%20that%20use%20it%20to%20learn%20everything%2C%20and%20those%20that%20use%20it%20so%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20learn%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20Cuban%20said%20of%20large%20language%20models%20in%20an%20X%20post%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECuban%20has%20previously%20said%20that%20AI%20models%20can't%20provide%20all%20the%20answers%20and%20are%20%26quot%3Bstupid%26quot%3B%20but%20like%20%26quot%3Ba%20savant%20that%20remembers%20everything.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20June%20conference%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20French%20AI%20lab%20Mistral%20said%20that%20a%20risk%20of%20using%20AI%20for%20everything%20is%20that%20humans%20will%20stop%20trying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20risk%20with%20AI%20is%20not%20that%20it%20will%20outsmart%20us%20or%20become%20uncontrollable%2C%20but%20that%20it%20will%20make%20us%20too%20comfortable%2C%20too%20dependent%2C%20and%20ultimately%20too%20lazy%20to%20think%20or%20act%20for%20ourselves%2C%26quot%3B%20Arthur%20Mensch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepmind-ceo-demis-hassabis-ai-lazy-way-hurts-thinking-skills-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771563661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6997cd63a645d1188189a604%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeepmind-ceo-demis-hassabis-ai-lazy-way-hurts-thinking-skills-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20DeepMind%20CEO%20said%20that%20AI%20is%20like%20the%20internet%20%E2%80%94%20people%20can%20use%20it%20to%20learn%20all%20kinds%20of%20topics%2C%20or%20use%20it%20in%20ways%20that%20%26quot%3Bdegrade%2