20about%20Charles'%20affair.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAndrew%20Mountbatten-Windsor%20was%20arrested%20on%20Thursday%20on%20suspicion%20of%20misconduct%20in%20public%20office.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20centuries%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Froyal-family-tree-british-monarchy-house-of-windsor-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBritish%20royal%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20cultivated%20an%20image%20of%20duty%20and%20decorum.%20As%20public%20figures%2C%20they've%20also%20had%20their%20share%20of%20scandals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForbidden%20romances%2C%20tabloid%20firestorms%2C%20and%20allegations%20of%20misconduct%20have%20rocked%20the%20House%20of%20Windsor%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20look%20at%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20scandals%20involving%20royal%20family%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EKing%20Edward%20VIII%20rejected%20the%20crown%20in%201936%20so%20he%20could%20marry%20a%20divorced%20American%20woman.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222824%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wallis%20Simpson%20and%20Edward%20VIII%20pose%20for%20a%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5841edd670296621008b4d05%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222118%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWallis%20Simpson%20and%20Edward%20VIII.%3Cp%3ELen%20Putnam%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDirectly%20after%20his%20father%20died%20in%201936%2C%20Edward%20VIII%20took%20the%20throne.%20Less%20than%20a%20year%20later%2C%20he%20renounced%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20he%20had%20fallen%20hard%20for%20Wallis%20Simpson%2C%20an%20American%20socialite%20who'd%20already%20been%20divorced%20once%20and%20was%20working%20through%20her%20second.%20His%20proposal%20of%20marriage%20caused%20social%20and%20political%20uproar%2C%20since%20the%20Church%20of%20England%20technically%20forbade%20Edward%20from%20marrying%20someone%20who'd%20been%20divorced.%20Eventually%2C%20Edward%20was%20forced%20to%20abdicate.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20found%20it%20impossible%20to%20carry%20the%20heavy%20burden%20of%20responsibility%20and%20to%20discharge%20my%20duties%20as%20King%20%5B...%5D%20without%20the%20help%20and%20support%20of%20the%20woman%20I%20love%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20radio%20address%20to%20the%20nation%20in%20December%201936.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEdward%20and%20Simpson%20married%20in%201937%20and%20stayed%20together%20until%20Edward's%20death%20in%201972.%20(And%20she%20wasn't%20the%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F18-commoners-who-married-into-royalty-2016-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommoner%20who%20married%20into%20royalty%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPrincess%20Margaret%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20a%20married%20man.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Captain%20Peter%20Townsend%20stands%20behind%20Princess%20Margaret.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F583871bc65edfe22008b4aa5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECaptain%20Peter%20Townsend%20and%20Princess%20Margaret.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECaptain%20Peter%20Townsend%20was%20a%20Royal%20Air%20Force%20officer%20who%20served%20as%20an%20equerry%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%20an%20attendant%20to%20the%20royal%20family.%20He%20spent%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20time%20with%20Margaret%2C%20and%20before%20long%2C%20the%20two%20fell%20in%20love.%20The%20only%20problem%20was%20that%20he%20was%20married.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20got%20even%20more%20scandalous%20in%201953%20when%20Townsend%20divorced%20his%20wife%20and%20proposed%20to%20Margaret%2C%20but%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20Church%20of%20England%20forbade%20such%20a%20marriage.%20(After%20all%2C%20Margaret's%20uncle%20Edward%20VIII%20had%20to%20relinquish%20the%20throne%20in%20order%20to%20marry%20a%20divorcee.)%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20relationship%20came%20to%20a%20heartbreaking%20close%20in%201955%20when%20they%20called%20off%20the%20engagement.%20There%20was%20simply%20no%20way%20for%20Captain%20Townsend%20and%20Princess%20Margaret%20to%20have%20a%20happy%20ending.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHer%20eventual%20marriage%20to%20a%20different%20man%20ended%20in%20a%20high-profile%20divorce.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222292%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Princess%20Margaret%20and%20Anthony%20Armstrong%20Jones%20in%201960.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5846dad665edfed50a8b4eb2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221719%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrincess%20Margaret%20and%20Anthony%20Armstrong%20Jones.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20long%20after%20calling%20things%20off%20with%20Townsend%2C%20Margaret%20married%20photographer%20Anthony%20Armstrong%20Jones.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-royal-weddings-of-all-time-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroyal%20wedding%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20ever%20be%20televised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20later%2C%20their%20union%20became%20a%20source%20of%20%26quot%3Bgrowing%20public%20ridicule%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2002%2F02%2F10%2Fworld%2Fprincess-margaret-dies-at-71-sister-of-queen-elizabeth-had-a-troubled-life.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20They%20fought%20in%20public%2C%20Margaret%20took%20long%20vacations%20without%20her%20husband%2C%20and%20rumors%20swirled%20around%20her%20close%20friendship%20with%20a%20man%2017%20years%20her%20junior.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201976%2C%20the%20couple%20announced%20their%20separation%2C%20and%20two%20years%20later%2C%20they%20were%20officially%20divorced.%20Margaret%20became%20the%20first%20royal%20to%20divorce%20since%20Henry%20VIII%2C%20who%20reigned%20way%20back%20in%20the%201500s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPrincess%20Diana%20and%20an%20alleged%20lover%20were%20secretly%20recorded%20on%20the%20phone.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20side%20by%20side%20image%20of%20Princess%20Diana%20and%20James%20Gilbey.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5841f4ff65edfe1b008b4e7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrincess%20Diana%20and%20James%20Gilbey.%3Cp%3EKimimasa%20Mayama%2FReuters%3B%20David%20Jones%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201992%20%E2%80%94%20while%20then-%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-royal-weddings-of-all-time-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrince%20Charles%20and%20Princess%20Diana%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20still%20married%20%E2%80%94%20media%20outlets%20published%20the%20transcript%20of%20a%20conversation%20between%20Diana%20and%20an%20alleged%20lover%20named%20James%20Gilbey.%20In%20the%20conversation%2C%20Gilbey%20told%20Diana%20that%20he%20loved%20her%20and%20called%20her%20by%20the%20pet%20name%20%26quot%3BSquidgy%26quot%3B%2053%20times.%20That's%20how%20the%20scandal%20earned%20the%20memorable%20moniker%20%26quot%3BSquidgygate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20in%20an%20interview%2C%20Diana%20confirmed%20that%20the%20conversation%20was%20real%2C%20but%20denied%20that%20it%20was%20adulterous%20in%20nature.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20same%20thing%20happened%20to%20Diana's%20husband%2C%20Charles.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221745%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Camilla%20Parker%20Bowles%20and%20Prince%20Charles%20in%201999.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5841f6627029661c008b4d46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221309%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECamilla%20Parker%20Bowles%20and%20Prince%20Charles.%3Cp%3EAlistair%20Grant%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20long%20after%20Diana's%20leaked%20phone%20call%2C%20Charles%2C%20Queen%20Elizabeth's%20oldest%20son%2C%20had%20one%20of%20his%20own.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Australian%20magazine%20published%20the%20transcript%20of%20a%20call%20between%20Charles%20and%20Camilla%20Parker%20Bowles%20%E2%80%94%20a%20longtime%20married%20friend.%20The%20transcript%20all%20but%20confirmed%20what%20many%20rumors%20had%20postulated%3A%20That%20Charles%20and%20Camilla%20were%20romantically%20involved.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20more%20confounding%20parts%20of%20the%20conversation%2C%20the%20couple%20joked%20about%20Charles%20turning%20into%20a%20tampon%20in%20order%20to%20%26quot%3Blive%20inside%26quot%3B%20Camilla's%20trousers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20that%20year%2C%20Charles%20and%20Diana%20announced%20their%20separation.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThen%20Diana%20gave%20a%20bombshell%20TV%20interview%2C%20and%20the%20marriage%20collapsed%20for%20good.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221976%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Prince%20Charles%20and%20Princess%20Diana%20looking%20away%20from%20each%20other%20in%201992.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5841f80e7029661b008b4d10%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221482%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrince%20Charles%20and%20Princess%20Diana%20in%201992.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201995%2C%20Diana%20sat%20down%20for%20a%20tell-all%20solo%20interview%20with%20journalist%20Martin%20Bashir%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20immense%20pressures%20of%20public%20life%20and%20her%20struggles%20with%20self-harm%2C%20postpartum%20depression%2C%20and%20bulimia.%20She%20also%20revealed%20that%20she%20knew%20about%20Charles'%20affair%20with%20Camilla.%20(%26quot%3BThere%20were%20three%20of%20us%20in%20this%20marriage%2C%20so%20it%20was%20a%20bit%20crowded%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20famously%20quipped.)%20And%20Diana%20even%20admitted%20that%20she'd%20been%20unfaithful%20to%20Charles%2C%20saying%20that%20she%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bin%20love%26quot%3B%20with%20James%20Hewitt%2C%20her%20riding%20instructor.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20BBC%20interview%20itself%20has%20since%20come%20under%20scrutiny.%20An%20article%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Farticle%2Fbbc-journalist-martin-bashir-misled-dianas-brother-to-secure-bombshell-interview-2x6nj28jm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESunday%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202020%20alleged%20that%20Bashir%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmartin-bashir-quits-bbc-amid-inquiry-into-princess-diana-interview-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanipulated%20Diana%20into%20doing%20the%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20showing%20her%20brother%2C%20Charles%20Spencer%2C%20fake%20bank%20statements%20that%20purported%20to%20show%20the%20media%20had%20been%20paying%20royal%20associates%20for%20information%20about%20her.%20A%202021%20inquiry%20concluded%20that%20Bashir%20acted%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeceitful%26quot%3B%20way%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-57189371%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Bashir%20apologized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20weeks%20after%20the%20interview%2C%20the%20Queen%20herself%20urged%20her%20son%20and%20daughter-in-law%20to%20divorce%2C%20and%20the%20following%20year%2C%20they%20made%20it%20official.%20Charles%20and%20Camilla%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20wed%20in%202005%20and%20are%20still%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPrincess%20Anne%20divorced%20her%20husband%20and%20married%20a%20member%20of%20the%20royal%20staff.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222683%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mark%20Phillips%20and%20Princess%20Anne%20smile%20in%201976.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5841fd3665edfe1f008b4e48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222012%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMark%20Phillips%20and%20Princess%20Anne%20in%201976.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPrincess%20Anne%2C%20the%20only%20daughter%20of%20Queen%20Elizabeth%20II%2C%20married%20Olympic%20equestrian%20Mark%20Phillips%20in%201973.%20The%20couple%20spent%20large%20swaths%20of%20time%20apart%20and%20didn't%20appear%20to%20be%20happy%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fpeople.com%2Farchive%2Fcover-story-a-crisis-rocks-a-royal-marriage-vol-31-no-16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeople%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20described%20the%20marriage%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bjoyless%20sham.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%20spring%201989%2C%20a%20British%20newspaper%20obtained%20stolen%20copies%20of%20letters%20written%20to%20Anne%20by%20one%20of%20her%20equerries%2C%20a%20British%20naval%20officer%20named%20Timothy%20Laurence.%20Though%20the%20content%20of%20the%20letters%20wasn't%20made%20public%2C%20tabloids%20described%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20intimate%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btoo%20hot%20to%20handle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201992%2C%20Anne%20announced%20that%20she%20was%20divorcing%20Phillips%2C%20and%20that%20she%20planned%20to%20marry%20Laurence.%20The%20two%20have%20been%20together%20ever%20since.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPaparazzi%20caught%20Sarah%20Ferguson%20in%20a%20compromising%20%26quot%3Btoe-licking%26quot%3B%20incident.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222406%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sarah%20Ferguson%20in%201988.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5841fa9c65edfe1f008b4e44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221804%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESarah%20Ferguson.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Redman%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Ferguson%20(popularly%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BFergie%26quot%3B)%20married%20Queen%20Elizabeth's%20son%2C%20Andrew%20Mountbatten-Windsor%2C%20in%201986.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20years%20later%2C%20scandal%20erupted%3A%20Paparazzi%20photographers%20captured%20Fergie%20vacationing%20with%20an%20American%20financial%20advisor%20named%20John%20Bryan.%20In%20one%20photo%20%E2%80%94%20an%20image%20quickly%20plastered%20on%20the%20front%20page%20of%20The%20Sun%20%E2%80%94%20Bryan%20appeared%20to%20be%20licking%20Fergie's%20foot.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20didn't%20go%20very%20well%20after%20that.%20Fergie%20and%20Andrew%20separated%20in%201992%2C%20the%20same%20year%20as%20Charles%20and%20Diana%2C%20and%20divorced%20in%201996.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELater%2C%20Fergie%20was%20accused%20of%20taking%20a%20%24633%2C000%20bribe.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221421%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sarah%20Ferguson%20and%20Prince%20Andrew%20wave%20to%20the%20crowd%20on%20their%20wedding%20day%20in%201986.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5841fb9765edfe1a008b4ea4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221065%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESarah%20Ferguson%20and%20Prince%20Andrew%20on%20their%20wedding%20day%20in%201986.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFergie's%20marital%20drama%20didn't%20end%20after%20the%20divorce.%20In%202010%2C%20a%20News%20of%20the%20World%20journalist%20posed%20as%20a%20businessman%20and%20said%20he%20got%20Fergie%20to%20accept%20a%20%C2%A3500%2C00%20(about%20%24633%2C000)%20bribe%20in%20exchange%20for%20access%20to%20her%20ex-husband%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fuk%2F2010%2Fmay%2F23%2Fsarah-ferguson-andrew-cash-tabloid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20video%20recording%20of%20their%20meeting%20was%20released%20to%20the%20media%2C%20and%20Fergie%20later%20apologized%2C%20saying%20she'd%20made%20a%20%26quot%3Bserious%20lapse%20in%20judgment%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-britain-royal-sting-idUSTRE64M0Y220100523%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPrince%20Harry%20spent%20a%20day%20(yes%2C