22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227486%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20view%20of%20the%20Pentagon%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69962e14a645d11881898b6e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224211%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAerial%20view%20of%20the%20Pentagon%3Cp%3EDoD%20photo%20by%20U.S.%20Air%20Force%20Staff%20Sgt.%20John%20Wright%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Pentagon%20flagged%2033%20universities%20as%20risky%20for%20military%20education%20programs%2C%20per%20an%20internal%20Army%20email.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Defense%20Department%20has%20cut%20ties%20with%20Harvard%2C%20which%20the%20email%20identified%20as%20%26quot%3Bfully%20off%20limits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENo%20criteria%20were%20provided%20for%20risk%20assessments.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20is%20rethinking%20its%20ties%20with%20dozens%20of%20universities%2C%20which%20could%20affect%20tuition%20assistance%20and%20other%20programs%20for%20military%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Defense%20severed%20its%20ties%20with%20Harvard%20University%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20sharing%20that%20it%20was%20reviewing%20other%20schools%20as%20well.%20The%20Pentagon%20hasn't%20publicly%20identified%20the%20additional%20schools%20under%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20internal%20US%20Army%20email%20that%20leaked%20last%20week%20offers%20some%20indication%3A%20the%20message%20lists%2033%20private%20universities%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-reviews-schools-students-universities-uncertainty-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20Pentagon%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20labeled%20as%20%26quot%3Bmoderate%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bhigh%26quot%3B%20risk.%20The%20email%20did%20not%20explain%20what%20classifies%20a%20school%20as%20a%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProspective%20military%20students%20should%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bbackup%20plan%26quot%3B%20in%20case%20the%20Pentagon%20cuts%20ties%20with%20these%20schools%2C%20the%20email%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScreenshots%20of%20the%20message%20circulated%20online%20last%20week%2C%20catching%20many%20people%20by%20surprise.%20Universities%2C%20professors%2C%20and%20service%20members%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20felt%20blindsided.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internal%20email%20identified%20Harvard%20as%20%26quot%3Bfully%20off%20limits%26quot%3B%20to%20service%20members%20pursuing%20higher%20education%20through%20Department%20of%20Defense-funded%20programs.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhegseth-had-system-installed-for-personal-cell-in-pentagon-office-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDefense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20called%20Harvard%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20red-hot%20centers%20of%20Hate%20America%20activism%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20the%20Pentagon%20will%20not%20work%20with%20the%20university%20on%20professional%20military%20education%20programs%20and%20fellowships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Army%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20Defense%20Department%20is%20reviewing%20other%20schools%20beyond%20Harvard%2C%20but%20no%20further%20decisions%20have%20been%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20list%2C%20which%20a%20defense%20official%20told%20Business%20Insider%20remains%20%26quot%3Bup%20in%20the%20air%2C%26quot%3B%20contains%20Ivy%20League%20schools%20and%20other%20prominent%20institutions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20some%20lesser-known%20universities.%20Public%20schools%20are%20under%20review%20as%20well%2C%20an%20email%20said%2C%20though%20those%20schools%20were%20not%20listed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh-performing%20troops%20can%20apply%20to%20such%20institutions%20through%20competitive%20selection%20processes%20to%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-shocking-pentagon-firing-lawyers-not-top-generals-legal-experts-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emilitary%20attorneys%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20level%